Düsseldorf starts building its Grand Départ celebrations this week when Mythos Tour de France, an exhibition of work from world-renowned photographers and artists, opens at the NRW-Forum.

Work from the likes of Timm Kölln, whose post-race portrait of Mark Cavendish from his Rouleur-published book The Peloton is above, Olaf Unverzart and other fine photographers whose images have appeared in Rouleur over the last 10 years – including Magnum legends Robert Capa and Harry Gruyeart. The show also features work from Düsseldorf-based artist Reinhard Mucha and fellow city residents Kraftwerk. See rouleur.cc for further details
